1
00:00:14,244 --> 00:00:15,620
Natsumi!

2
00:00:17,372 --> 00:00:18,498
Natsumi!

3
00:00:20,291 --> 00:00:21,125
Sorry!

4
00:00:23,670 --> 00:00:24,587
Natsumi!

5
00:00:24,671 --> 00:00:25,547
Hey!

6
00:00:25,630 --> 00:00:28,133
-What are you doing? It's too dangerous!
-My daughter…

7
00:00:28,216 --> 00:00:30,593
-My daughter is inside!
-What?

8
00:00:31,386 --> 00:00:32,512
Natsumi!

9
00:00:58,705 --> 00:01:00,290
LOVE-CHAN COOKIE

10
00:01:04,586 --> 00:01:05,420
All right.

11
00:01:05,503 --> 00:01:07,005
See you all later.

12
00:01:07,088 --> 00:01:08,506
-See you.
-Good night.

13
00:01:08,590 --> 00:01:09,549
What?

14
00:01:09,632 --> 00:01:10,717
What's the rush?

15
00:01:11,217 --> 00:01:12,677
I just have a feeling.

16
00:01:12,760 --> 00:01:13,720
A feeling?

17
00:01:13,803 --> 00:01:17,473
A feeling that if I stay,
I'll get caught up in work.

18
00:01:17,557 --> 00:01:19,601
Don't jinx it at this hour.

19
00:01:19,684 --> 00:01:21,895
It was peaceful today, wasn't it?

20
00:01:21,978 --> 00:01:25,398
This is exactly when
sudden requests come in, right?

21
00:01:25,481 --> 00:01:27,567
That's what you call a sixth sense.

22
00:01:28,151 --> 00:01:31,487
It's said that the insular cortex
in the brain is involved in that.

23
00:01:31,571 --> 00:01:32,488
The insular cortex?

24
00:01:32,572 --> 00:01:36,117
It is a region involved in various
internal sensations of the body.

25
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:38,244
What seems like a hunch

26
00:01:38,328 --> 00:01:42,749
is actually detecting and anticipating
a change, based on past experiences.

27
00:01:42,832 --> 00:01:44,792
So there is a proper basis for it.

28
00:01:45,627 --> 00:01:46,461
I'm done too.

29
00:01:46,544 --> 00:01:47,378
Hey, wait!

30
00:01:47,462 --> 00:01:48,504
See you.

31
00:01:55,720 --> 00:01:57,639
Oh, good evening.

32
00:01:57,722 --> 00:01:58,681
Hey.

33
00:01:59,265 --> 00:02:00,892
Kerosene has been detected.

34
00:02:01,392 --> 00:02:02,560
It has to be arson.

35
00:02:02,644 --> 00:02:05,230
-Is this the body?
-Yes.

36
00:02:05,313 --> 00:02:07,315
It carbonized due to high temperatures,

37
00:02:07,398 --> 00:02:10,318
and then the house collapsed,
crushing the remains.

38
00:02:11,527 --> 00:02:15,490
The skeletal structure
hasn't retained its original form either.

39
00:02:15,573 --> 00:02:17,242
According to eyewitnesses,

40
00:02:17,325 --> 00:02:20,328
five-year-old Natsumi Sata
wasn't able to escape the house,

41
00:02:20,411 --> 00:02:22,247
and her mother, Haruka Sata,

42
00:02:22,330 --> 00:02:24,666
reportedly went into the fire
to try and save her.

43
00:02:25,833 --> 00:02:28,419
-Wait! Just wait!
-Let me through!

44
00:02:33,466 --> 00:02:36,135
That is Haruka's husband, Yasuyuki Sata.

45
00:02:37,053 --> 00:02:38,596
Excuse us.

46
00:02:39,180 --> 00:02:40,473
We're the police.

47
00:02:41,057 --> 00:02:43,685
Could we ask you a few questions?

48
00:02:44,185 --> 00:02:45,770
What on earth happened?

49
00:02:46,604 --> 00:02:48,147
Haruka and Natsumi are okay, right?

50
00:02:49,399 --> 00:02:50,316
Where are they?

51
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:52,694
We're still investigating the details.

52
00:02:53,194 --> 00:02:54,028
But we've found

53
00:02:54,946 --> 00:02:56,489
burned skeletal parts.

54
00:02:57,073 --> 00:03:01,119
Eyewitnesses report seeing
Haruka and Natsumi taken by the fire.

55
00:03:06,416 --> 00:03:07,750
That's not true.

56
00:03:09,836 --> 00:03:11,504
It can't be true.

57
00:03:13,381 --> 00:03:15,842
Natsumi! Haruka!

58
00:03:16,467 --> 00:03:17,969
Please calm down.

59
00:03:22,223 --> 00:03:23,558
There's no way…

60
00:03:25,226 --> 00:03:26,728
It's not true.

61
00:03:29,605 --> 00:03:30,857
Sir.

62
00:03:32,191 --> 00:03:35,153
I'm sorry for asking this
at such a difficult time.

63
00:03:35,653 --> 00:03:39,365
Do you recognize this?

64
00:03:40,533 --> 00:03:42,201
It's a wedding ring, isn't it?

65
00:03:46,497 --> 00:03:49,625
This belongs to Haruka, correct?

66
00:03:54,797 --> 00:03:56,341
I promise you.

67
00:03:57,717 --> 00:04:01,262
The police will get to the bottom of this.

68
00:04:16,611 --> 00:04:18,821
All the soft tissue was burnt away.

69
00:04:18,905 --> 00:04:21,157
We have to handle this quite carefully.

70
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:23,910
I wonder if any teeth marks are left.

71
00:04:23,993 --> 00:04:26,412
Can an accurate identification
really be made?

72
00:04:26,496 --> 00:04:31,459
Regardless of the body's condition,
a piece of the truth is always there.

73
00:04:40,676 --> 00:04:41,969
Let's begin.

74
00:04:49,268 --> 00:04:52,647
Personal identification
proved to be extremely difficult.

75
00:04:52,730 --> 00:04:54,190
However, this part,

76
00:04:54,273 --> 00:04:56,692
although severely damaged,

77
00:04:56,776 --> 00:04:59,070
appears to be the lower first molar.

78
00:04:59,153 --> 00:05:01,948
This is likely
a metallic inlay restoration.

79
00:05:02,031 --> 00:05:05,576
With this, we managed to match
the teeth marks with the dental charts,

80
00:05:05,660 --> 00:05:09,080
confirming that the body
belongs to Haruka Sata.

81
00:05:09,163 --> 00:05:10,957
You did a great job identifying it.

82
00:05:11,541 --> 00:05:14,502
Even looking at the femur,
which withstood the most,

83
00:05:14,585 --> 00:05:16,504
there is no mistake
that it's a female in her thirties.

84
00:05:16,587 --> 00:05:18,548
So, what about the child?

85
00:05:20,091 --> 00:05:21,467
About that…

86
00:05:23,970 --> 00:05:25,763
We couldn't find her.

87
00:05:25,847 --> 00:05:26,889
What?

88
00:05:28,391 --> 00:05:34,230
Currently, the gathered remains
are for only one person, Haruka.

89
00:05:34,313 --> 00:05:36,023
No way.

90
00:05:37,316 --> 00:05:40,862
But Haruka went into the fire
to save Natsumi, didn't she?

91
00:05:40,945 --> 00:05:44,157
A child calling for help inside the flames
was also witnessed.

92
00:05:44,240 --> 00:05:45,700
However,

93
00:05:45,783 --> 00:05:48,369
from those remains…

94
00:05:53,249 --> 00:05:55,209
Since she was still a small child,

95
00:05:55,293 --> 00:05:58,212
could it be that the bones
were completely destroyed?

96
00:05:59,463 --> 00:06:03,301
Even at the maximum temperature of
a crematorium, fragments of bone remain.

97
00:06:04,010 --> 00:06:07,555
It is impossible for absolutely
no trace to be left behind.

98
00:06:07,638 --> 00:06:09,515
Did she completely turn to ash?

99
00:06:09,599 --> 00:06:10,933
Even if reduced to ash,

100
00:06:11,017 --> 00:06:13,311
inorganic matter
derived from bone remains.

101
00:06:13,394 --> 00:06:16,606
It becomes a powder,
but some trace should still be left.

102
00:06:16,689 --> 00:06:18,149
It doesn't add up.

103
00:06:18,232 --> 00:06:20,484
Of course, I suppose
there is a possibility

104
00:06:20,568 --> 00:06:25,573
that she escaped the flames on her own
and is alive somewhere.

105
00:06:25,656 --> 00:06:27,783
There were many onlookers
around the scene,

106
00:06:27,867 --> 00:06:29,911
and a fire truck arrived
on the back street.

107
00:06:29,994 --> 00:06:32,288
Nobody witnessed a child escaping.

108
00:06:32,872 --> 00:06:35,583
Then, where is Natsumi?

109
00:06:38,044 --> 00:06:40,254
She vanished into the fire.

110
00:06:41,255 --> 00:06:42,340
Is that it?

111
00:06:44,050 --> 00:06:45,593
For now,

112
00:06:46,969 --> 00:06:48,304
it's a mystery.

113
00:06:49,555 --> 00:06:51,349
Kozue Tanahara.

114
00:06:51,432 --> 00:06:55,853
You were the first caller
for yesterday's fire, correct?

115
00:06:55,937 --> 00:06:56,938
Yes.

116
00:06:57,021 --> 00:07:01,275
It seems you reported
that your friend jumped into the flames.

117
00:07:01,776 --> 00:07:02,985
A friend?

118
00:07:03,069 --> 00:07:03,986
Right.

119
00:07:04,695 --> 00:07:08,532
Haruka and I have been partners
in badminton since we were young.

120
00:07:09,450 --> 00:07:10,993
We were always together.

121
00:07:11,577 --> 00:07:13,955
It seems like you did rather well.

122
00:07:15,373 --> 00:07:16,958
What's this photo?

123
00:07:17,667 --> 00:07:20,336
That was when we went
to a hot spring last year.

124
00:07:22,797 --> 00:07:25,383
You were with Haruka
yesterday as well, correct?

125
00:07:28,261 --> 00:07:31,180
Please tell us what happened.

126
00:07:35,434 --> 00:07:36,852
<i>Yesterday,</i>

127
00:07:36,936 --> 00:07:41,857
<i>we were driving in my car</i>
<i>just to get a change of pace.</i>

128
00:07:41,941 --> 00:07:43,401
<i>And then,</i>

129
00:07:43,484 --> 00:07:45,695
<i>when I dropped her off at her house…</i>

130
00:07:46,862 --> 00:07:47,989
Help!

131
00:07:48,531 --> 00:07:49,907
It's hot!

132
00:07:53,369 --> 00:07:54,579
Mom!

133
00:07:54,662 --> 00:07:55,580
Haruka?

134
00:07:55,663 --> 00:07:56,956
Help me!

135
00:07:57,582 --> 00:07:58,666
Natsumi!

136
00:08:02,253 --> 00:08:03,254
Natsumi!

137
00:08:03,337 --> 00:08:05,798
-Hey! What are you doing?
-My daughter…

138
00:08:05,881 --> 00:08:07,174
It's hot!

139
00:08:07,258 --> 00:08:09,010
My daughter is inside!

140
00:08:09,093 --> 00:08:10,177
It's too dangerous!

141
00:08:10,261 --> 00:08:11,345
Natsumi!

142
00:08:20,646 --> 00:08:21,647
I can't believe it.

143
00:08:22,648 --> 00:08:24,650
You didn't find Natsumi?

144
00:08:29,614 --> 00:08:31,324
Just to confirm,

145
00:08:32,742 --> 00:08:35,286
Natsumi was left home alone?

146
00:08:36,287 --> 00:08:37,121
Yes.

147
00:08:39,498 --> 00:08:41,500
Where did you go?

148
00:08:42,793 --> 00:08:45,254
We didn't really have any destination.

149
00:08:45,338 --> 00:08:46,464
We just wanted to talk.

150
00:08:46,547 --> 00:08:48,174
Just talk?

151
00:08:49,675 --> 00:08:52,053
Like about what happened at kindergarten.

152
00:08:52,762 --> 00:08:54,055
And about Yasuyuki.

153
00:08:54,138 --> 00:08:56,098
Who is Yasuyuki?

154
00:08:56,766 --> 00:08:57,892
<i>Haruka's husband.</i>

155
00:08:58,392 --> 00:09:01,270
Yasuyuki and I
were originally high school classmates,

156
00:09:01,354 --> 00:09:03,022
and I introduced him to Haruka.

157
00:09:04,982 --> 00:09:07,234
So you were the one
who brought them together.

158
00:09:17,161 --> 00:09:18,663
Are we about done now?

159
00:09:19,288 --> 00:09:21,123
I have an appointment coming up.

160
00:09:21,207 --> 00:09:23,584
You're not taking time off from work, huh?

161
00:09:24,168 --> 00:09:25,086
What?

162
00:09:25,169 --> 00:09:27,129
Your close friend passed away.

163
00:09:27,922 --> 00:09:29,548
You must be shaken up.

164
00:09:33,886 --> 00:09:35,388
Well, I'm busy.

165
00:09:36,972 --> 00:09:40,351
More importantly, have Natsumi's remains
still not been found?

166
00:09:40,434 --> 00:09:41,936
Please find them quickly.

167
00:09:43,688 --> 00:09:44,897
Of course.

168
00:09:44,980 --> 00:09:46,440
I'm counting on you.

169
00:09:48,025 --> 00:09:48,901
Of course.

170
00:09:49,527 --> 00:09:50,695
We will do our best.

171
00:09:57,493 --> 00:09:58,828
<i>Natsumi was only five.</i>

172
00:09:58,911 --> 00:10:02,123
Leaving such a young child alone
just for a casual drive is strange.

173
00:10:02,206 --> 00:10:05,209
-They could've taken her along.
-Well, that's true.

174
00:10:05,292 --> 00:10:06,127
That's true.

175
00:10:06,210 --> 00:10:09,547
And her friend died,
yet she didn't ask a single question.

176
00:10:09,630 --> 00:10:12,133
"Why did she die?" "Who did it?"
People ask that.

177
00:10:12,758 --> 00:10:14,135
Are you saying

178
00:10:14,677 --> 00:10:16,512
you suspect Kozue is the arsonist?

179
00:10:22,143 --> 00:10:24,186
Investigate Kozue Tanahara thoroughly.

180
00:10:24,270 --> 00:10:25,104
Yes, ma'am.

181
00:10:36,824 --> 00:10:38,159
The next batch has arrived.

182
00:10:38,242 --> 00:10:39,201
All right.

183
00:10:40,453 --> 00:10:41,454
What?

184
00:10:41,537 --> 00:10:44,749
Are we checking all of this to see
if we find Natsumi's remains?

185
00:10:44,832 --> 00:10:48,210
They said they had everything
that looked strange transported here.

186
00:10:48,294 --> 00:10:50,755
This is definitely not bone.

187
00:10:51,464 --> 00:10:52,548
Right this way.

188
00:10:54,258 --> 00:10:56,135
These are Haruka's parents.

189
00:11:05,436 --> 00:11:06,729
Is this

190
00:11:07,438 --> 00:11:08,773
our daughter?

191
00:11:10,941 --> 00:11:12,067
Most likely.

192
00:11:13,777 --> 00:11:15,154
What about Nat-chan?

193
00:11:17,114 --> 00:11:18,782
She hasn't been found yet.

194
00:11:54,777 --> 00:11:59,114
Haruka would always send us photos.

195
00:12:01,242 --> 00:12:03,118
Most of them were of Nat-chan.

196
00:12:05,788 --> 00:12:07,373
She's so cute.

197
00:12:09,041 --> 00:12:10,751
She took everything,

198
00:12:11,252 --> 00:12:13,420
anything that could be a memento.

199
00:12:14,213 --> 00:12:18,842
She often complained
that she had too many things at home.

200
00:12:18,926 --> 00:12:20,135
Just the other day,

201
00:12:21,053 --> 00:12:23,430
she brought a memento box to our house.

202
00:12:23,514 --> 00:12:25,057
A memento box?

203
00:12:27,643 --> 00:12:31,605
If it's all right, could we borrow that?

204
00:12:32,106 --> 00:12:33,023
What?

205
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:37,486
It seems Natsumi's remains
still haven't been found.

206
00:12:37,570 --> 00:12:40,906
Is it even possible not to find them
after searching this much?

207
00:12:40,990 --> 00:12:42,324
I wonder.

208
00:12:43,284 --> 00:12:46,328
Could a kidnapper
have taken advantage of the fire?

209
00:12:46,829 --> 00:12:49,123
It's not impossible. But…

210
00:12:51,875 --> 00:12:53,627
something feels off.

211
00:12:55,921 --> 00:12:57,089
I forgot to mention.

212
00:12:57,590 --> 00:13:00,467
I was staking out
Kozue Tanahara's apartment.

213
00:13:01,969 --> 00:13:04,555
I know, about you and Haruka.

214
00:13:04,638 --> 00:13:06,098
And you?

215
00:13:07,308 --> 00:13:09,059
You're relieved, aren't you?

216
00:13:10,227 --> 00:13:11,312
What?

217
00:13:12,521 --> 00:13:14,607
You wanted to break up with her, right?

218
00:13:15,441 --> 00:13:18,360
With this, the obstacle is finally gone.

219
00:13:20,362 --> 00:13:21,614
You…

220
00:13:21,697 --> 00:13:23,073
Aren't you glad?

221
00:13:25,451 --> 00:13:27,828
<i>It seems the two of them</i>
<i>were having an affair.</i>

222
00:13:27,911 --> 00:13:30,372
A witness report came
from Yasuyuki's colleague

223
00:13:30,456 --> 00:13:34,877
that he brought a woman along
to his business trip destination.

224
00:13:35,961 --> 00:13:39,340
Out of growing love and hatred
for her best friend's husband,

225
00:13:39,423 --> 00:13:42,926
Kozue Tanahara killed Natsumi,
who became an obstacle, by arson.

226
00:13:43,010 --> 00:13:46,388
Furthermore, she enticed Haruka
to save Natsumi,

227
00:13:46,472 --> 00:13:48,515
causing her death.

228
00:13:51,477 --> 00:13:54,021
So, what do you think?

229
00:14:02,821 --> 00:14:03,656
Hey.

230
00:14:03,739 --> 00:14:06,575
Couldn't this potentially be
a child's temporal bone?

231
00:14:09,078 --> 00:14:11,538
It looks like an adult's cheekbone to me.

232
00:14:11,622 --> 00:14:15,626
No, but, Haruka fractured a bone
last month from falling down the stairs.

233
00:14:15,709 --> 00:14:18,754
If it's her cheekbone,
shouldn't there be a surgical plate?

234
00:14:22,633 --> 00:14:24,009
Is it this one?

235
00:14:24,510 --> 00:14:25,427
Hey.

236
00:14:27,054 --> 00:14:28,305
It's this one.

237
00:14:28,389 --> 00:14:29,556
MEDICAL RECORD

238
00:14:29,640 --> 00:14:31,225
FIXED CHEEK WITH SURGICAL PLATE

239
00:14:31,308 --> 00:14:32,559
FELL DOWN STAIRS AT HER HOME

240
00:14:32,643 --> 00:14:33,894
FELL DOWN STAIRS

241
00:14:33,978 --> 00:14:36,855
In any case, it's not a child's bone.

242
00:14:36,939 --> 00:14:37,815
It's not, right?

243
00:14:37,898 --> 00:14:39,525
-It's not.
-It's impossible!

244
00:14:41,902 --> 00:14:43,278
Dr. Masumi.

245
00:14:43,862 --> 00:14:47,741
It seems Natsumi's remains
really can't be found after all.

246
00:14:48,993 --> 00:14:50,536
Is that so?

247
00:14:51,286 --> 00:14:53,122
Huh? What's this?

248
00:14:53,205 --> 00:14:56,291
Oh, it's Natsumi's memento box.

249
00:14:58,544 --> 00:15:00,170
-So cute.
-Wow.

250
00:15:00,254 --> 00:15:02,089
Oh, that's right.

251
00:15:02,172 --> 00:15:03,257
Look.

252
00:15:04,591 --> 00:15:05,676
What is that?

253
00:15:06,260 --> 00:15:07,761
It's an umbilical cord.

254
00:15:07,845 --> 00:15:09,847
Oh, from when Natsumi was born?

255
00:15:09,930 --> 00:15:10,764
Yes.

256
00:15:10,848 --> 00:15:12,558
I figured she would have kept it.

257
00:15:12,641 --> 00:15:14,643
This will be useful too.

258
00:15:15,227 --> 00:15:16,562
Useful?

259
00:15:16,645 --> 00:15:19,648
To match Natsumi's DNA.

260
00:15:19,732 --> 00:15:22,151
Please test if a sample can be collected.

261
00:15:22,234 --> 00:15:23,318
Okay.

262
00:15:26,488 --> 00:15:27,489
Ms. Kiryu.

263
00:15:27,573 --> 00:15:30,909
Please go to the police station
and get the list of missing persons.

264
00:15:30,993 --> 00:15:33,996
A similar case
might provide some sort of hint.

265
00:15:34,079 --> 00:15:35,998
Right, I'm on it.

266
00:15:39,126 --> 00:15:40,502
MISSING PERSON REPORT

267
00:15:40,586 --> 00:15:43,338
I haven't been able to contact my daughter
for three days.

268
00:15:43,422 --> 00:15:45,924
Her workplace says
they can't reach her either.

269
00:15:46,008 --> 00:15:47,551
That is worrying.

270
00:15:48,635 --> 00:15:50,846
Do you remember what
she might have been wearing?

271
00:15:50,929 --> 00:15:52,431
Supervisor!

272
00:15:55,809 --> 00:15:58,812
I'd have it sent to you
if you'd asked me about it.

273
00:15:59,813 --> 00:16:00,689
I'm sorry.

274
00:16:02,858 --> 00:16:05,778
So, how is the case going?

275
00:16:06,487 --> 00:16:08,697
Any clues?

276
00:16:18,165 --> 00:16:21,502
Where could Natsumi have disappeared to?

277
00:16:28,300 --> 00:16:29,468
Ms. Dojima?

278
00:16:33,514 --> 00:16:34,556
It's just…

279
00:16:37,684 --> 00:16:38,977
The police

280
00:16:40,270 --> 00:16:43,482
exist to protect people's loved ones.

281
00:16:47,069 --> 00:16:49,029
People's loved ones…

282
00:16:54,618 --> 00:16:56,120
Hurry up.

283
00:16:57,246 --> 00:16:58,247
Yes, ma'am.

284
00:17:00,541 --> 00:17:02,960
Here is the list of missing persons.

285
00:17:03,043 --> 00:17:04,044
Thank you very much.

286
00:17:04,128 --> 00:17:06,463
Well, I'm heading out for the day.

287
00:17:06,547 --> 00:17:08,173
Oh? It's still early.

288
00:17:12,010 --> 00:17:13,804
I'm going to meet a man.

289
00:17:14,304 --> 00:17:16,140
What? A man?

290
00:17:18,892 --> 00:17:20,144
Oh, wow.

291
00:17:21,728 --> 00:17:23,856
Ms. Dojima met someone nice, huh?

292
00:17:25,232 --> 00:17:26,400
Well…

293
00:17:26,483 --> 00:17:28,360
That's not what she meant.

294
00:17:29,361 --> 00:17:30,195
What?

295
00:17:30,904 --> 00:17:32,322
He's a senior detective.

296
00:17:33,198 --> 00:17:35,659
She says he always looked after her.

297
00:17:35,742 --> 00:17:39,246
What she just said was also a teaching
from that senior officer.

298
00:17:39,329 --> 00:17:43,125
Despite how she may seem,
when she was young,

299
00:17:43,208 --> 00:17:46,879
she didn't do well in the male-dominated
police force, and it troubled her.

300
00:17:47,963 --> 00:17:49,089
<i>At that time,</i>

301
00:17:49,590 --> 00:17:51,925
<i>she had failed to apprehend a suspect.</i>

302
00:17:59,516 --> 00:18:01,518
I heard you let the suspect get away.

303
00:18:03,812 --> 00:18:05,355
I am very sorry.

304
00:18:07,149 --> 00:18:08,567
What's wrong with that?

305
00:18:09,151 --> 00:18:10,194
What?

306
00:18:12,905 --> 00:18:15,908
You were protecting the family
present at the scene

307
00:18:15,991 --> 00:18:17,201
and let him go, right?

308
00:18:21,038 --> 00:18:22,206
That's fine.

309
00:18:23,332 --> 00:18:27,211
We are here to protect
people's loved ones.

310
00:18:29,254 --> 00:18:30,839
You're suited to be a detective.

311
00:18:32,507 --> 00:18:35,677
You probably won't get promoted, though.

312
00:18:36,303 --> 00:18:37,429
Just like me.

313
00:19:05,624 --> 00:19:07,042
<i>But that senior officer,</i>

314
00:19:08,543 --> 00:19:11,421
<i>while trying to protect a child</i>
<i>from a random attacker…</i>

315
00:19:16,718 --> 00:19:18,136
<i>was killed in the line of duty.</i>

316
00:19:20,639 --> 00:19:24,935
<i>Since then, whenever something happens,</i>
<i>she goes to his grave.</i>

317
00:19:26,645 --> 00:19:30,440
I think he's the only person
Ms. Dojima can ask for advice from.

318
00:20:08,312 --> 00:20:10,230
MAHO KIRYU

319
00:20:23,285 --> 00:20:24,202
Dr. Masumi!

320
00:20:26,663 --> 00:20:28,040
Look at this.

321
00:20:28,540 --> 00:20:29,750
-Ms. Dojima!
-What?

322
00:20:29,833 --> 00:20:33,211
Regarding Kozue Tanahara,
she's taking paid leave starting tomorrow.

323
00:20:34,046 --> 00:20:35,172
Oh, really?

324
00:20:35,255 --> 00:20:37,049
Do you think she intends to flee?

325
00:20:37,132 --> 00:20:38,675
Seems suspicious, right?

326
00:20:38,759 --> 00:20:40,010
-That's true.
-Also--

327
00:20:40,093 --> 00:20:42,262
Tell me once you've found any evidence.

328
00:20:43,263 --> 00:20:44,306
I have.

329
00:20:45,432 --> 00:20:49,603
One hour before the arson occurred,
Kozue Tanahara purchased kerosene.

330
00:20:51,980 --> 00:20:54,566
Why don't you bring that up first?!

331
00:20:54,649 --> 00:20:55,525
Sorry!

332
00:20:57,235 --> 00:21:00,238
We extracted DNA from both
the umbilical cord and the remains

333
00:21:00,322 --> 00:21:04,117
to perform an STR analysis,
and there were ten mismatches.

334
00:21:05,035 --> 00:21:05,994
Excuse me?

335
00:21:06,078 --> 00:21:09,998
In other words, biologically,
there is no parent-child relationship.

336
00:21:10,082 --> 00:21:11,208
What?

337
00:21:11,792 --> 00:21:14,086
Dr. Masumi, what does this mean?

338
00:21:23,345 --> 00:21:24,638
DENTAL RECORDS

339
00:21:46,076 --> 00:21:48,995
<i>Her mother, Haruka Sata,</i>
<i>reportedly went into the fire.</i>

340
00:21:49,079 --> 00:21:51,665
<i>The gathered remains</i>
<i>are for only one person.</i>

341
00:21:51,748 --> 00:21:53,208
<i>I have an appointment coming up.</i>

342
00:21:53,291 --> 00:21:56,086
<i>We managed to match the teeth marks</i>
<i>with the dental charts.</i>

343
00:22:07,097 --> 00:22:10,434
Please examine the remains once more.

344
00:22:13,437 --> 00:22:14,688
Could it be…

345
00:22:15,814 --> 00:22:17,232
The pieces

346
00:22:18,358 --> 00:22:20,152
might be coming together.

347
00:22:39,129 --> 00:22:40,380
Hello.

348
00:22:40,463 --> 00:22:42,048
Do you have a moment?

349
00:23:00,859 --> 00:23:02,194
Sorry to keep you waiting.

350
00:23:02,777 --> 00:23:04,988
Sorry, I know you were about to go out.

351
00:23:06,323 --> 00:23:08,283
Where were you planning to go?

352
00:23:10,076 --> 00:23:11,578
Nowhere in particular.

353
00:23:12,287 --> 00:23:15,081
A lot has happened,
just wanted to refresh myself.

354
00:23:15,165 --> 00:23:16,833
Either way, what is this about?

355
00:23:18,460 --> 00:23:20,212
We have found out

356
00:23:20,712 --> 00:23:23,965
that the deceased body was not Haruka.

357
00:23:30,805 --> 00:23:32,265
The victim's identity

358
00:23:33,183 --> 00:23:34,434
is Miwa Tateno.

359
00:23:35,894 --> 00:23:40,023
She is a high school classmate
of yours and Yasuyuki's.

360
00:23:41,107 --> 00:23:46,154
Miwa's whereabouts had been unknown
since the day of that fire.

361
00:23:46,655 --> 00:23:49,199
I haven't been able to contact my daughter
for three days.

362
00:23:49,282 --> 00:23:50,200
MIWA TATENO

363
00:23:50,283 --> 00:23:51,868
That is only natural.

364
00:23:52,661 --> 00:23:53,828
Because

365
00:23:54,829 --> 00:23:59,751
the body found at the scene of the fire
was not Haruka's,

366
00:24:01,711 --> 00:24:03,463
but Miwa's.

367
00:24:08,260 --> 00:24:09,427
<i>As you are friends,</i>

368
00:24:09,511 --> 00:24:13,848
<i>both of them were visiting</i>
<i>the dental clinic you manage.</i>

369
00:24:14,849 --> 00:24:17,394
<i>Using your position,</i>

370
00:24:17,477 --> 00:24:19,646
<i>you swapped the dental charts</i>

371
00:24:20,230 --> 00:24:22,065
<i>and disguised Miwa's body</i>

372
00:24:22,148 --> 00:24:24,901
<i>as Haruka's body.</i>

373
00:24:27,487 --> 00:24:28,989
I don't know anything about that.

374
00:24:29,072 --> 00:24:30,448
That's nonsense.

375
00:24:30,532 --> 00:24:35,287
The first thing I found strange
was the photo from the hot spring trip.

376
00:24:36,037 --> 00:24:39,499
<i>In that photo,</i>
<i>Haruka was not wearing a wedding ring.</i>

377
00:24:39,582 --> 00:24:43,003
<i>It seems she hadn't worn a ring</i>
<i>for several years.</i>

378
00:24:43,586 --> 00:24:48,758
Then why was she wearing it
at the time of the fire?

379
00:24:52,220 --> 00:24:53,805
That's what made me think.

380
00:24:54,306 --> 00:24:58,768
Did someone perhaps
deliberately put the ring on Miwa

381
00:24:58,852 --> 00:25:00,729
to disguise her?

382
00:25:04,691 --> 00:25:08,111
There is only one person
who could make such a disguise

383
00:25:08,194 --> 00:25:11,948
using a wedding ring
found somewhere in the house.

384
00:25:17,120 --> 00:25:18,163
That would be…

385
00:25:20,874 --> 00:25:22,000
Haruka herself.

386
00:25:22,083 --> 00:25:23,376
That's not true!

387
00:25:25,295 --> 00:25:26,546
It was me.

388
00:25:27,172 --> 00:25:28,631
I did everything.

389
00:25:34,637 --> 00:25:36,514
In this arson case,

390
00:25:37,140 --> 00:25:40,477
the two of you conspired together.

391
00:25:43,104 --> 00:25:46,816
So, why did you do such a thing?

392
00:25:48,568 --> 00:25:52,864
<i>Haruka visited several orthopedic clinics</i>
<i>over the past few years.</i>

393
00:25:53,365 --> 00:25:55,658
<i>Her fracture from the fall</i>
<i>seemed unnatural,</i>

394
00:25:55,742 --> 00:25:59,287
<i>and she had bruises that looked</i>
<i>as if she had been punched.</i>

395
00:26:02,248 --> 00:26:06,336
It seems Haruka was being
physically abused by Yasuyuki.

396
00:26:07,003 --> 00:26:09,881
And you knew about it, right?

397
00:26:09,964 --> 00:26:11,800
I already told you I did it!

398
00:26:13,885 --> 00:26:17,013
Since I'm admitting to it,
just hurry up and arrest me!

399
00:26:24,896 --> 00:26:27,357
The one who killed Miwa Tateno

400
00:26:28,274 --> 00:26:29,442
was neither you

401
00:26:30,235 --> 00:26:31,486
nor Haruka.

402
00:26:32,445 --> 00:26:33,530
Isn't that right?

403
00:26:36,324 --> 00:26:39,494
We obtained a warrant
and checked your dashcam.

404
00:26:41,579 --> 00:26:43,206
On the day of the incident,

405
00:26:43,289 --> 00:26:47,627
you two didn't want anyone to hear you
discussing the domestic abuse.

406
00:26:48,962 --> 00:26:50,547
That's why you went for a drive.

407
00:26:52,424 --> 00:26:54,509
You should really just go to the police.

408
00:26:55,093 --> 00:26:56,428
The police?

409
00:26:57,929 --> 00:26:59,556
But if I do that,

410
00:27:00,306 --> 00:27:02,976
he really will kill me.

411
00:27:06,896 --> 00:27:08,731
But you have to run away.

412
00:27:11,526 --> 00:27:12,986
I can't.

413
00:27:14,612 --> 00:27:16,030
No matter where I go,

414
00:27:17,532 --> 00:27:19,284
he will chase me down.

415
00:27:23,538 --> 00:27:25,582
<i>Contrary to your statement,</i>

416
00:27:25,665 --> 00:27:28,835
<i>Natsumi was actually with you.</i>

417
00:27:29,961 --> 00:27:30,920
<i>And…</i>

418
00:27:31,504 --> 00:27:36,217
<i>when you went to drop off</i>
<i>Haruka and Natsumi…</i>

419
00:27:36,301 --> 00:27:37,802
There we go.

420
00:27:37,886 --> 00:27:39,345
What snack do you want?

421
00:27:42,891 --> 00:27:44,058
What's wrong?

422
00:27:45,977 --> 00:27:46,811
Natsumi.

423
00:27:46,895 --> 00:27:49,564
-Yes?
-Wash your hands and go upstairs.

424
00:28:01,326 --> 00:28:02,494
She's dead.

425
00:28:04,621 --> 00:28:05,914
The police…

426
00:28:06,789 --> 00:28:07,957
This is Miwa.

427
00:28:09,292 --> 00:28:10,251
What?

428
00:28:11,252 --> 00:28:12,670
You know her?

429
00:28:13,671 --> 00:28:15,590
We were classmates in high school.

430
00:28:15,673 --> 00:28:17,300
She comes to the clinic.

431
00:28:17,884 --> 00:28:19,511
Why is she…

432
00:28:20,678 --> 00:28:22,680
Anyway, the police…

433
00:28:22,764 --> 00:28:23,973
Wait!

434
00:28:28,561 --> 00:28:30,021
We have to do it.

435
00:28:30,730 --> 00:28:32,440
This is your only chance.

436
00:28:35,401 --> 00:28:36,236
Kozue?

437
00:28:39,155 --> 00:28:40,198
Haruka…

438
00:28:41,324 --> 00:28:42,700
You should die.

439
00:28:44,953 --> 00:28:46,746
What are you saying?

440
00:28:47,789 --> 00:28:50,041
We'll make it look like you died.

441
00:28:50,667 --> 00:28:53,169
Then, you can be reborn.

442
00:28:57,382 --> 00:28:58,633
And then,

443
00:28:59,133 --> 00:29:03,555
you two immediately
went through with the plan.

444
00:29:06,266 --> 00:29:11,187
<i>First, you got Natsumi out to the car</i>
<i>in a nearby parking lot.</i>

445
00:29:13,439 --> 00:29:14,357
<i>Then,</i>

446
00:29:15,066 --> 00:29:16,734
<i>you put on the wedding ring.</i>

447
00:29:18,987 --> 00:29:22,740
<i>And to completely burn away the body,</i>
<i>you doused her in kerosene.</i>

448
00:29:50,310 --> 00:29:51,311
Natsumi!

449
00:29:51,394 --> 00:29:52,478
My daughter…

450
00:29:52,562 --> 00:29:55,189
-My daughter is inside!
-What?

451
00:29:56,816 --> 00:29:59,736
<i>Of course, you could not fake</i>
<i>a child's remains.</i>

452
00:29:59,819 --> 00:30:02,572
<i>Therefore, you reported</i>
<i>to the fire department</i>

453
00:30:02,655 --> 00:30:05,199
<i>that you saw Natsumi</i>
<i>trapped inside the house.</i>

454
00:30:06,117 --> 00:30:06,951
There's a fire.

455
00:30:07,035 --> 00:30:09,704
A girl is trapped inside,
and my friend went in there.

456
00:30:09,787 --> 00:30:10,914
Please hurry!

457
00:30:11,623 --> 00:30:16,336
<i>And, she escaped from the back door</i>
<i>before the fire truck arrived.</i>

458
00:30:17,211 --> 00:30:21,716
<i>She met up with Natsumi</i>
<i>and escaped in your car.</i>

459
00:30:28,139 --> 00:30:33,853
At first, we thought that you
and Yasuyuki were having an affair.

460
00:30:34,979 --> 00:30:36,814
But that wasn't the case.

461
00:30:38,316 --> 00:30:39,359
Kozue.

462
00:30:40,443 --> 00:30:41,486
You…

463
00:30:43,613 --> 00:30:46,157
were trying to protect Haruka
and Natsumi, right?

464
00:30:46,240 --> 00:30:47,325
No!

465
00:30:48,284 --> 00:30:50,244
Quit saying all this nonsense!

466
00:30:50,328 --> 00:30:52,622
I did everything, it was me!

467
00:30:54,707 --> 00:30:56,709
Haruka has nothing to do with it.

468
00:30:56,793 --> 00:30:58,503
Haruka… Haruka is…

469
00:30:58,586 --> 00:31:00,755
Your beloved partner.

470
00:31:02,256 --> 00:31:03,341
Right?

471
00:31:05,760 --> 00:31:07,178
She's the partner

472
00:31:08,262 --> 00:31:11,474
you've been fighting together with
all along, isn't she?

473
00:31:35,164 --> 00:31:36,290
I'm sorry.

474
00:31:40,253 --> 00:31:41,713
Haruka, I'm sorry.

475
00:31:43,589 --> 00:31:45,466
I couldn't protect you.

476
00:31:55,351 --> 00:31:56,561
You were

477
00:31:57,603 --> 00:32:00,940
about to go see Haruka
and her daughter, weren't you?

478
00:32:03,109 --> 00:32:05,820
Could you tell us their location?

479
00:32:08,740 --> 00:32:12,285
What will happen to Natsumi
if just the two of us are arrested?

480
00:32:14,787 --> 00:32:16,664
At this rate, Yasuyuki will…

481
00:32:16,748 --> 00:32:18,041
Don't worry.

482
00:32:18,875 --> 00:32:20,752
I won't let that happen.

483
00:32:21,586 --> 00:32:26,299
The police exist to protect
your loved ones.

484
00:32:27,175 --> 00:32:29,052
We will protect her.

485
00:32:30,678 --> 00:32:32,055
Please trust us.

486
00:32:55,578 --> 00:32:56,662
Go ahead.

487
00:32:58,539 --> 00:32:59,582
What?

488
00:32:59,665 --> 00:33:01,292
You found Natsumi?

489
00:33:01,375 --> 00:33:02,627
Yes.

490
00:33:02,710 --> 00:33:05,505
Where is she? Please let me see her.

491
00:33:05,588 --> 00:33:06,589
More importantly,

492
00:33:08,132 --> 00:33:13,846
there is suspicion against you
for physically abusing Haruka.

493
00:33:16,474 --> 00:33:17,975
What are you talking about?

494
00:33:19,018 --> 00:33:20,728
I would never do that.

495
00:33:24,857 --> 00:33:28,027
Sure, we've had a couple of
marital disputes before.

496
00:33:29,487 --> 00:33:32,532
But anyone has those, don't they?

497
00:33:34,200 --> 00:33:35,493
Either way,

498
00:33:35,993 --> 00:33:37,954
please tell me where Natsumi is.

499
00:33:39,038 --> 00:33:41,415
She is my dearest daughter.

500
00:33:43,167 --> 00:33:44,919
I need to be with her.

501
00:33:45,002 --> 00:33:46,462
I can't do that.

502
00:33:47,880 --> 00:33:49,090
Why not?

503
00:33:49,590 --> 00:33:51,467
Because you

504
00:33:52,802 --> 00:33:55,555
are the person who killed Miwa Tateno.

505
00:33:58,224 --> 00:34:02,395
You and Miwa had been having an affair
since last year's alumni association.

506
00:34:02,478 --> 00:34:03,354
This way, please.

507
00:34:04,897 --> 00:34:05,857
Thank you.

508
00:34:10,027 --> 00:34:13,406
<i>But she became dissatisfied</i>
<i>with that relationship…</i>

509
00:34:13,489 --> 00:34:14,365
What's wrong?

510
00:34:14,448 --> 00:34:16,659
No, nothing. What shall we eat?

511
00:34:16,742 --> 00:34:20,371
<i>…and her behavior gradually escalated.</i>

512
00:34:22,290 --> 00:34:25,543
We have also found the message exchange
between Miwa and you.

513
00:34:26,043 --> 00:34:27,461
On the night of the incident,

514
00:34:27,545 --> 00:34:30,047
while Haruka and her daughter were away,

515
00:34:30,131 --> 00:34:32,592
she seems to have barged into your house.

516
00:34:34,719 --> 00:34:36,762
Cut it out already.

517
00:34:37,263 --> 00:34:40,224
Since you can't seem to break up yourself,

518
00:34:40,725 --> 00:34:42,602
I will tell your wife.

519
00:34:42,685 --> 00:34:44,020
Stop joking.

520
00:34:45,479 --> 00:34:47,315
I'm being serious!

521
00:34:47,398 --> 00:34:51,611
Shall I just go tell her myself,
or will you divorce her?

522
00:34:51,694 --> 00:34:53,237
Decide, now!

523
00:34:56,699 --> 00:34:57,909
Or…

524
00:35:01,996 --> 00:35:03,497
shall we die together?

525
00:35:33,903 --> 00:35:35,821
<i>After you ran away,</i>

526
00:35:35,905 --> 00:35:39,158
<i>you must have been surprised</i>
<i>to hear Haruka died in the fire.</i>

527
00:35:39,242 --> 00:35:42,745
Eyewitnesses report seeing
Haruka and Natsumi taken by the fire.

528
00:35:44,205 --> 00:35:45,539
That's not true.

529
00:35:47,750 --> 00:35:49,543
It can't be true.

530
00:35:49,627 --> 00:35:53,506
<i>But upon seeing the wedding ring,</i>
<i>which she shouldn't have been wearing,</i>

531
00:35:54,090 --> 00:35:56,676
<i>you realized the swap Haruka pulled off.</i>

532
00:35:57,635 --> 00:35:58,719
<i>And then, you…</i>

533
00:35:59,303 --> 00:36:00,429
I know about you and Haruka.

534
00:36:00,513 --> 00:36:01,806
And you?

535
00:36:03,099 --> 00:36:04,600
You're relieved, aren't you?

536
00:36:05,184 --> 00:36:06,769
The reason you went to see Kozue

537
00:36:07,270 --> 00:36:12,984
was actually to get the whereabouts
of Haruka and your daughter, wasn't it?

538
00:36:18,864 --> 00:36:19,991
I admit

539
00:36:20,783 --> 00:36:24,036
that I ended up in that kind
of relationship with Miwa.

540
00:36:24,870 --> 00:36:25,788
But,

541
00:36:26,789 --> 00:36:28,499
I didn't kill her or anything.

542
00:36:30,835 --> 00:36:33,212
There's not a single piece
of evidence, right?

543
00:36:34,463 --> 00:36:39,302
Because it all vanished in the fire.

544
00:36:48,519 --> 00:36:49,854
There is.

545
00:36:51,564 --> 00:36:52,940
We've got evidence.

546
00:36:57,278 --> 00:37:02,074
Where did you go after leaving the scene
following the murder?

547
00:37:02,783 --> 00:37:03,993
Upon investigation,

548
00:37:04,910 --> 00:37:07,455
we found out you went
to a home improvement center.

549
00:37:09,040 --> 00:37:12,001
You purchased plastic buckets,
a shovel, and so on.

550
00:37:12,084 --> 00:37:12,918
Also,

551
00:37:13,502 --> 00:37:16,213
a large amount of industrial caustic soda.

552
00:37:16,297 --> 00:37:17,798
WORKERS HEAVEN
RECEIPT

553
00:37:17,882 --> 00:37:22,094
Originally used
for industrial cleaning tasks,

554
00:37:22,595 --> 00:37:25,765
it seems it also has the effect
of dissolving skin and protein.

555
00:37:26,891 --> 00:37:31,896
Did you intend
to dissolve and dispose of the body?

556
00:37:32,480 --> 00:37:33,564
No.

557
00:37:34,482 --> 00:37:35,608
That's…

558
00:37:35,691 --> 00:37:37,193
That's not all.

559
00:37:42,114 --> 00:37:45,284
Our colleagues were persistent

560
00:37:45,368 --> 00:37:47,995
and examined the remains
over and over again.

561
00:37:49,663 --> 00:37:53,209
When analyzing the internal structure
with a micro-CT,

562
00:37:53,292 --> 00:37:58,047
we found a depression mark on the skull
that cannot be explained by heat.

563
00:38:01,634 --> 00:38:06,222
<i>It was a very small trace</i>
<i>that wouldn't normally be found.</i>

564
00:38:07,431 --> 00:38:08,849
<i>But because of how skilled they are,</i>

565
00:38:08,933 --> 00:38:10,768
<i>they were able to find it.</i>

566
00:38:12,978 --> 00:38:15,314
Next is the identification
of the murder weapon.

567
00:38:15,981 --> 00:38:17,775
Next is the culprit.

568
00:38:19,402 --> 00:38:23,531
They will not give up until they solve it.

569
00:38:31,330 --> 00:38:33,124
I promised you, didn't I?

570
00:38:33,207 --> 00:38:35,918
That we would get to the bottom of this.

571
00:38:37,711 --> 00:38:42,174
We will definitely protect them.

572
00:39:13,706 --> 00:39:14,957
Wait!

573
00:39:15,040 --> 00:39:17,585
Yasuyuki admitted to the crime.

574
00:39:18,335 --> 00:39:19,503
Of course,

575
00:39:19,587 --> 00:39:23,007
you two also need to atone
for a serious crime,

576
00:39:23,841 --> 00:39:28,888
but I think he will be in prison
for a long time for murder.

577
00:39:34,518 --> 00:39:36,312
Thank you very much.

578
00:39:38,063 --> 00:39:39,356
Really.

579
00:39:40,649 --> 00:39:41,567
Not at all.

580
00:39:47,031 --> 00:39:48,199
Kozue…

581
00:39:54,288 --> 00:39:55,456
Thank you.

582
00:40:57,518 --> 00:41:00,187
Finally, we're done.

583
00:41:01,605 --> 00:41:03,232
Shall we take a break?

584
00:41:03,315 --> 00:41:04,316
Yes.

585
00:41:04,400 --> 00:41:06,485
Everyone, you all did such a great job.

586
00:41:06,569 --> 00:41:08,237
Yes, we seriously did.

587
00:41:08,320 --> 00:41:10,906
I'm really glad the case was solved.

588
00:41:10,990 --> 00:41:13,659
I wonder if our investigation was useful.

589
00:41:13,742 --> 00:41:16,078
I don't want to search
for anything for a while.

590
00:41:16,161 --> 00:41:17,955
If you would like, please have some.

591
00:41:18,831 --> 00:41:19,748
What?

592
00:41:19,832 --> 00:41:21,500
Love-chan cookies.

593
00:41:21,584 --> 00:41:23,877
-Cute.
-I've been hooked on them lately.

594
00:41:23,961 --> 00:41:25,254
Cookies, huh?

595
00:41:25,337 --> 00:41:26,171
Thank you.

596
00:41:26,255 --> 00:41:27,840
-Thank you!
-Go ahead.

597
00:41:27,923 --> 00:41:30,342
Since everyone overused
their prefrontal cortex,

598
00:41:30,426 --> 00:41:32,469
the brain must be craving sugar.

599
00:41:32,553 --> 00:41:34,054
I get that.

600
00:41:34,138 --> 00:41:36,015
-I'll have one more.
-Go ahead.

601
00:41:36,599 --> 00:41:39,101
You did a great job too, Ms. Kiryu.

602
00:41:41,604 --> 00:41:42,855
Thank you very much.

603
00:41:50,779 --> 00:41:53,949
Somebody's loved one.

604
00:42:00,205 --> 00:42:01,248
Everyone

605
00:42:02,124 --> 00:42:04,793
felt the same way, huh?

606
00:42:32,154 --> 00:42:33,656
TAKASAKA FAMILY GRAVE

607
00:42:33,739 --> 00:42:37,826
We are here to protect
people's loved ones.

608
00:42:39,953 --> 00:42:41,622
You're suited to be a detective.

609
00:42:52,633 --> 00:42:55,844
Why did you have to die so soon?

610
00:43:11,527 --> 00:43:13,696
What you said before

611
00:43:14,196 --> 00:43:16,073
about the meaning of a "loved one"…

612
00:43:17,032 --> 00:43:18,367
In America,

613
00:43:19,201 --> 00:43:22,705
they call the deceased a "loved one."

614
00:43:23,539 --> 00:43:25,332
Does that mean someone…

615
00:43:27,000 --> 00:43:28,877
who was important…

616
00:43:30,212 --> 00:43:31,714
to someone else?

617
00:43:34,133 --> 00:43:36,176
I feel like I've also…

618
00:43:37,845 --> 00:43:41,682
managed to grasp
what that means to me, just a bit.

619
00:43:43,183 --> 00:43:44,351
That

620
00:43:44,852 --> 00:43:46,395
is a wonderful thing.

621
00:43:59,783 --> 00:44:02,327
Rock, paper, scissors, shoot! It's a tie!

622
00:44:02,411 --> 00:44:04,496
Rock, paper, scissors, shoot!

623
00:44:06,206 --> 00:44:07,958
Okay, one more time.

624
00:44:08,041 --> 00:44:09,251
Let's do it.

625
00:44:09,334 --> 00:44:10,252
All right!

626
00:44:11,086 --> 00:44:13,130
One, two! Rock, paper, scissors, shoot.

627
00:44:13,213 --> 00:44:14,381
It's a tie.

628
00:44:14,465 --> 00:44:16,049
Yes!

629
00:44:16,133 --> 00:44:18,510
One, two! Rock, paper, scissors, shoot!

630
00:44:20,637 --> 00:44:22,723
<i>If he'd asked someone for help,</i>

631
00:44:22,806 --> 00:44:24,057
<i>he might not have died.</i>

632
00:44:24,141 --> 00:44:26,226
<i>Can you cook next week, too?</i>

633
00:44:26,310 --> 00:44:28,103
You can still start over.

634
00:44:28,187 --> 00:44:31,440
<i>Mr. Susaki wasn't alone, was he?</i>

635
00:44:31,523 --> 00:44:35,027
<i>We have officially decided</i>
<i>to disband the MEJ.</i>

636
00:44:48,165 --> 00:44:51,001
Subtitle translation by: Maslin F.

